                <p><pb n="5"/> The Indians, on the borders of Kentucky, <lb/>continue to commit the most horrible acts of cruel<lb break="no"/>ty upon such unfortunate Americans as fall in <lb/>their power. The burning of the Miami villages, <lb/>and the destruction of their corn and vegetables, <lb/>instead of intimidating those ferocious savage, <lb/>have made them more and more vindictive and <lb/>restless; and being acquainted with all the passes <lb/>in the country, they bid defiance to their pursuers, <lb/>whom they frequently surprise and cut off.</p>
